      "alt": "❯ hiya claude we're going to build a Top Chicken labeller for bluesky and host it on\n  railway\n\n⏺ ruffles feathers, assumes a roosting position\n\n  hell yes. a Top Chicken labeller. let me make sure I'm building the right bird before\n  I start slinging code.\n\n  Quick mental model so we're aligned: a Bluesky labeller is an atproto service tied to\n  a labeler-account DID, whose DID doc points at an #atproto_labeler service endpoint.\n  It serves com.atproto.label.queryLabels + subscribeLabels, signs labels with the\n  account's signing key, and stores emitted labels somewhere (SQLite by default). Users\n  subscribe to it in-app and then see your label badges. The standard fun-labeller\n  toolchain is @skyware/labeler (server + setup CLI) optionally paired with @skyware/bot\n  for interaction-driven labelling — I'll verify that's still current before\n  committing.\n\n  The thing I genuinely don't know is what makes a chicken Top — i.e. the labelling\n  mechanism and the label set. That changes the whole architecture, so let me ask rather\n  than guess:",
